Pronunciation[edit]

(Classical) IPA(key): /ˈproː.fe.roː ˈdi.ɡi.tum/, [ˈproː.fɛ.roː ˈd̪ɪ.ɡɪ.t̪ʊ̃ˑ]

  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈpro.fe.ro ˈdi.d͡ʒi.tum/, [ˈprɔː.fɛ.rɔ ˈd̪iː.d͡ʒi.t̪um]

Verb[edit]

prōferō digitum (present infinitive prōferre digitum, perfect active prōtulī digitum, supine prōlātum digitum); third conjugation, irregular

  1. I lift a finger; make minimal effort.
